title: For Sale:  EARLY Mossberg .22 Target Rifle
postcontent:
For sale is my Mossberg model U.S.(a). This is a very early example, with a prototype first model front sight. Probably one of the first hundred or so made. From what I can tell, t was manufactured circa 1940. It has no serial numbers.

These rifles are legendary for their accuracy. The US military used them for training rifles in WWII. These rifles came factory tapped for scope mounts. I bought at new mount and new scope for the rifle, and it also comes with the original prototype peep sight. It also has a bull barrel.

The bore is in good shape. The rifle shoots .5" groups at 25 yards. I've taken it squirrel hunting the past few years, though it is heavy. Overall condition I would say is good. Plum patina covers all exposed metal parts, and the walnut stock is worn. The rifle isn't beat up, it just has a lot of character! When I bought it, I took it apart and there were little bits of hay on the inside. In its past, I think it spent some time as a barn gun.

I'm asking $400 for this rifle. Please text/call me at REDACTED anytime. Thanks!

(Please check my other listing of my Krag Jorgensen!)
